        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=5187&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=A+long+long+time+ago%2E%2E%2E%2E"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">On a server far, far away I started a gnome necro on Povar.  It was a dark time, yet exciting because everything was new. And, in the beginning Necros and Druids ruled the land for nothing could withstand their skilled Kiting.</P><P>And the masses whined...yet 80% played necros/druid.</P><P>Then Warriors were upgraded with quests, criticals, and other neat stuff.  So, the masses started a warrior.</P><P>And Then </P><P>Rogues were upgraded with poison and other neat skills, so the masses started a rogue</P><P>And then</P><P>Shaman were upgraded with a working alchemy and better pets so the masses started a shaman</P><P>And then </P><P>Paineel was added.  So everyone started and Erud SK...for a week.</P><P>And then</P><P>Kunark came.  So, the masses started an iksar monk.  Humans moaned.</P><P>BUT</P><P>Then people said, dear god we need more tanks, healers, and chanters.  50+ mobs really hurt.</P><P>More warriors, clerics, and chanters were made.</P><P>Then Velious came.</P><P>All other classes whined at the holy trinity.</P><P>Spells were fixed and added to give druids a reason to level past 51 as they can heal better.</P><P>Wizards came into their own.</P><P>Rogues became the dealers of monstrous damage.</P><P>Monks wept, but were given higher weight limits.</P><P>Magicians were given cool new toys - the best DOT in game, a useful tool (COH), monstrous epic reward, sow & unfear for pet, haste spell & item for pet</P><P>Sk's became nastiness</P><P>And VI looked and saw that it was good.  For the 80% necros/druid were now 4% 55-60.  </P><P>Logic train....<zoooom>...drat..missed it</P><P>2 classes should comprise 14% given an equal distribution.</P><P>Sigh, what was my point again?  I don't know.  Was talking with a friend over lunch about the history of the game and all the classes.  How all other classes have received more and more, making them better and yet the necro was the only one which has received less and less.</P><P>Just feeling shafted.  Shrug.  Oh well, back to powerleveling my gnome warrior.</P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>

